To implement the changes, I will update `types.ts` to include the `workflowSteps` definition, populate the project data in `constants.ts` with specific workflow steps and icons, and finally redesign the `Portfolio.tsx` component to render an interactive-looking workflow diagram for each project instead of static images.

# Updated files:

## types.ts

Added `workflowSteps` to `Project` interface.

```tsx
import React from 'react';

export interface Project {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  category: string;
  description: string;
  image: string;
  tools: string[];
  stat: string;
  workflowSteps: {
    icon: React.ElementType;
    label: string;
  }[];
}

export interface Service {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  icon: React.ElementType;
  features: string[];
}

export interface Testimonial {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  role: string;
  company: string;
  quote: string;
  avatar: string;
}

export enum ChatSender {
  USER = 'user',
  BOT = 'bot',
}

export interface ChatMessage {
  id: string;
  sender: ChatSender;
  text: string;
}
```

## constants.ts

Updated `PROJECTS` with specific `workflowSteps` and added necessary icon imports.

